# {{WORKSPACE_NAME}} — Docs

Shared documentation tracker for the **{{WORKSPACE_NAME}}** workspace.

When provisioned in `sibling` or `path` mode, this repository sits at the
workspace-parent level, alongside the meta-repo, package repos, and project
repos. It is its own git repository so documentation history can be versioned
and synced independently of the source code.

When provisioned in `symlink` mode, this folder is a symbolic link to an
external directory shared across multiple checkouts (e.g. across worktrees or
branch-specific clones).

## Layout

```
Docs/
├── architecture/   # high-level architecture, component diagrams, ADRs
├── api/            # API contracts, OpenAPI specs, integration notes
├── guides/         # how-to guides, onboarding, runbooks
└── notes/          # working notes, research, drafts
```

Subfolders are conventional, not enforced — adapt to the workspace's needs.

## Conventions

- Markdown only. One topic per file. Short, descriptive filenames.
- Cross-link related code in the corresponding package or project repo using
  relative paths from this repo's root (`../packages/<name>/...` or
  `../<project-repo>/...`).
- Architecture decision records: `architecture/adr-NNN-<slug>.md`.
